      • loadAuthenticationPlugins

        private void loadAuthenticationPlugins()
                                throws java.sql.SQLException
        Fill the authenticationPlugins map. First this method fill the map with instances of MysqlOldPasswordPlugin, MysqlNativePasswordPlugin, MysqlClearPasswordPlugin and Sha256PasswordPlugin. Then it gets instances of plugins listed in "authenticationPlugins" connection property by Util.loadExtensions(Connection, Properties, String, String, ExceptionInterceptor) call and adds them to the map too. The key for the map entry is getted by AuthenticationPlugin.getProtocolPluginName(). Thus it is possible to replace built-in plugin with custom one, to do it custom plugin should return value "mysql_native_password", "mysql_old_password", "mysql_clear_password" or "sha256_password" from it's own getProtocolPluginName() method. All plugin instances in the map are initialized by Extension.init(Connection, Properties) call with this.connection and this.connection.getProperties() values.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        True if plugin is default, false if plugin is not default.
        Throws:

      • getAuthenticationPlugin

        private AuthenticationPlugin getAuthenticationPlugin(java.lang.String pluginName)
                                              throws java.sql.SQLException
        Get authentication plugin instance from authenticationPlugins map by pluginName key. If such plugin is found it's AuthenticationPlugin.isReusable() method is checked, when it's false this method returns a new instance of plugin and the same instance otherwise. If plugin is not found method returns null, in such case the subsequent behavior of handshake process depends on type of last packet received from server: if it was Auth Challenge Packet then handshake will proceed with default plugin, if it was Auth Method Switch Request Packet then handshake will be interrupted with exception.
        Parameters:
        pluginName - mysql protocol plugin names, for example "mysql_native_password" and "mysql_old_password" for built-in plugins
        Returns:
        null if plugin is not found or authentication plugin instance initialized with current connection properties
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • appendCharsetByteForHandshake

        private void appendCharsetByteForHandshake(Buffer packet,
                                 java.lang.String enc)
                                    throws java.sql.SQLException
        Append the MySQL collation index to the handshake packet. A single byte will be added to the packet corresponding to the collation index found for the requested Java encoding name. If the index is > 255 which may be valid at some point in the future, an exception will be thrown. At the time of this implementation the index cannot be > 255 and only the COM_CHANGE_USER rpc, not the handshake response, can handle a value > 255.
        Parameters:
        packet - to append to
        end - The Java encoding name used to lookup the collation index
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
